A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 6A of Title 12 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 outdoor stewardship, so as to eliminate reductions in appropriations; to provide for related
3 matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
5 SECTION 1.
6 Chapter 6A of Title 12 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to outdoor
7 stewardship, is amended by revising Code Section 12-6A-5, relating to establishment of the
8 Georgia Outdoor Stewardship Trust Fund, as follows:
9 "12-6A-5.
10 (a) There is established the Georgia Outdoor Stewardship Trust Fund as a separate fund
11 in the state treasury. Except as provided in subsections (c) and (d) of this Code section, the
12 The General Assembly shall appropriate to the trust fund 40 percent of all moneys received
13 by the state from the sales and use tax collected by establishments classified under the 2007
14 North American Industry Classification Code 451110, sporting goods stores, in the most
15 recently completed fiscal year.
