16 (b) Such funds shall not lapse to the general fund. Such funds shall be used to support the
17 protection and conservation of land and shall be used to supplement, not supplant,
18 department resources.
19 (c)(1) In the event that, in any current fiscal year, the most recently completed fiscal
20 year's total moneys received from the levy of a sales and use tax fall at least 1 percent
21 below the total moneys received from the levy of the tax in the year prior to the most
22 recently completed fiscal year, then the amount that the General Assembly shall
23 appropriate to the trust fund for the following fiscal year shall be reduced by 20 percent.
24 (2) In the event that, in a fiscal year following the fiscal year of an initial trust fund
25 appropriation reduction pursuant to paragraph (1) of this subsection, the most recently
26 completed fiscal year's total moneys received from the levy of a sales and use tax fall at
27 least 1 percent below the total moneys received from the levy of the tax in the year prior
28 to the most recently completed fiscal year, then the amount that the General Assembly
29 shall appropriate to the trust fund for the following fiscal year shall be reduced by 50
30 percent.
31 (d) In any current fiscal year following a year for which the amount appropriated to the
32 trust fund is reduced in accordance with subsection (c) of this Code section, the same
33 percentage reduction shall continue unless the total moneys received from the levy of the
34 sales and use tax in the most recently completed fiscal year equal or exceed the total
35 moneys received from the levy of the sales and use tax in the most recent fiscal year in
36 which no reduction in the amount appropriated to the trust fund occurred pursuant to
37 subsection (c) or (d) of this Code section."
38 SECTION 2.
39 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
